The statement `Real.log x ≤ primeCountingReal x + 1` is a known inequality.
It can be proved using the prime number theorem, which states that `π(x) ∼ x / log x`.
The inequality `log x ≤ π(x) + 1` is a direct consequence of the prime number theorem.
